South Africa has recorded 926 new coronavirus cases. This brings the total number of cases to 682 215. The country has also recorded 40 new COVID-19 related fatalities, bringing the total number of deaths to 17 016. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in the Free State. “Regrettably, we report 40 more COVID-19 related deaths: “12 from Eastern Cape, 14 from Free State, 5 from Gauteng, 5 from Mpumalanga and 4 from Western Cape,” says Dr Mkhize. The cumulative number of tests conducted to date is 4 280 340. The number of recoveries now stands at 615 684, this translates to a recovery rate of 90%. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 682 215, the total number of deaths is 17 016 and the total number of recoveries is 615 684. pic.twitter.com/eM5HQ1FnRg — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) October 5, 2020 